wikipedia_page.main: Frederick William Millett   (30 March 1928 – 30 April 1991) was an English cricketer. A right-handed batsman and right-arm off-break bowler, he played for Cheshire from 1949 to 1972, captaining them from 1960 to 1970. In 210 Minor Counties Championship matches, he scored 8432 runs and took 300 wickets.
